---
description: Required development workflow for this repository
alwaysApply: true
---

All completed code changes must end with:

1. successful build
2. git add .
3. git commit with a clear message
4. git push

Do not leave work only in local uncommitted state.

Use commit prefixes like:
- feature:
- fix:
- ui:
- refactor:
- docs:
- chore:
- feat(...):
- fix(...):

After completing work, summarize:
- files changed
- build result
- commit message
- push result

If a change affects product behavior, also summarize:
- routes changed
- user-facing UX changes
- data model changes if relevant

Preferred workflow:
- work on branch when appropriate
- push branch
- verify preview deploy
- merge when build passes

If the user explicitly asks to keep work only local, follow that instruction for that task only.
